#24.Twister Prime Number
A Twister Prime number is a number where:
The number is prime
Its reverse is also prime

import java.util.*;
public class Main {

    static boolean isPrime(int n) {

        if(n <= 1)
            return false;

        for(int i = 2; i <= n/2; i++) {
            if(n % i == 0)
                return false;
        }

        return true;
    }

    public static void main(String args[]) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = sc.nextInt();

        int temp = n;
        int reverse = 0;

        while(temp > 0) {
            int digit = temp % 10;
            reverse = reverse * 10 + digit;
            temp = temp / 10;
        }

        if(isPrime(n) && isPrime(reverse)) {
            System.out.println("Twister Prime number");
        }
        else {
            System.out.println("Not a Twister Prime number");
        }

        sc.close();
    }
}

#25.Java Program on Twin Prime Number
Two numbers are called Twin Prime numbers if:
Both numbers are prime
Difference between them is 2
Example:
(5, 7) → both prime and difference = 2 → Twin Prime

